observations.recommendation:
We recommended to the Management:
*To instruct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to fully transfer the unutilized balances of LDRRMF for CY 2018 and its prior years from the General Fund to the Special Trust Fund in the total amount of P10,566,391.50 in accordance with the above cited provisions to properly monitor the utilization of the unspent LDRRMF;

*The Municipal Accountant shall observe the requirements set forth under COA Circular No. 2012-002 specifically the guidelines on the accounting and reporting of LDRRMF to ascertain that the financial information on LDRRMF is taken up appropriately in the books and properly disclosed in the Financial Statements.

In view of the foregoing, we recommended that:

The Municipality Treasurer stop disbursements for materials and labor in relation to Cabuntog Lodge project until an approved program of works is obtained;
The BAC strictly adheres to the Revised IRR of RA 9184 with regard to its procurement activities and take note of the following:
b.1) Prepare the Annual Procurement Plan (APP) and determine the appropriate Procurement modality then submit to the HOPE and/or other oversight bodies for approval;
b.2) Ensure that all procurement course through them and be done through competitive bidding, except when circumstances warrant alternative modes of procurement;
b.3) Avoid splitting of government contracts and purchase orders as these practices are against Section 54.1 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184 and COA Circular 76-41.
c. The Municipal Mayor, Municipal Treasurer and Municipal Accountant-Designate render written justification on the splitting of requisitions and payments for the Cabuntog Lodge project; and 
d. The Municipal Accountant-Designate ensure the completeness of documentary requirements as required in COA Circular 2021-001 before signing disbursements vouchers. Likewise, ensure that Purchase Orders contains requisite information as provided in Item VIII of COA Circular 97-004.

We recommended and the Management agreed to:

Provide sufficient funding not only from local sources of the LGU but also secure grants from other government agencies;
Strictly monitor wastes stored in the Barangay MRFs and consistently implement segregation;
Prioritize the acquisition of equipment necessary in the collection, processing and disposal operations; and 
Require the Barangay SWM Committees to perform its functions in accordance with RA 9003.

We recommended that Management:
*Stop the practice of charging expenses to LDRRMF which are not related to the purpose for which the fund is set for;
*Exert effort to immediately replenish the amount of ₱1,449,600.00 from the General fund back to LDRRMF and; 
*Instruct the Budget Office to strictly monitor the charges of all the funds of the Municipality.

We recommended and Management agreed to:

*Stop the granting of additional cash advances to officials and employees with outstanding balances;

*Retrieve the Disbursement Vouchers pertaining to cash advances and its corresponding Liquidation Reports of the reported UCAs but without supporting DVs and other documents; 

*Trace the documents in the recording of the cash advances and its liquidation; 

*Reconcile the reported amount in the Status on Unliquidated Cash Advances and the Statement of Financial Position as of December 31, 2017;

*Strictly enforce the liquidation and collection of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

*The Municipal Accountant shall demand for the liquidation of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;

*In the subsequent granting of cash advances and in order to prevent the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances, the Municipal Accountant shall send within ten (10) days before the expiration of the 30 days period written notices/reminders and letters enjoining the officers and employees to liquidate their travel cash advances.

We recommended and Management agreed with the following: 

*In the disbursement of government funds, the Municipality shall provide the necessary supporting documents as required under COA Circular No. 2012-001 and in compliance with Sections 4(6) and 7 of P.D. 1445;

*Require the recipient schools to submit a liquidation report to the accounting office;

*Stop the practice of charging expenses to LDRRMF which are not related to the purpose for which the fund is set for;
*Exert effort to immediately replenish the amount of P1,449,600.00 from the General fund back to LDRRMF account and;
*Instruct the Budget Office to strictly monitor the charges of all the funds of the Municipality.

*Stop the granting of additional cash advances to officials and employees with outstanding balances;
*Retrieve the Disbursement Vouchers pertaining to cash advances and its corresponding Liquidation Reports of the reported UCAs but without supporting DVs and other documents;
*Trace the documents in the recording of the cash advances and its liquidation;
*Reconcile the reported amount in the Status on Unliquidated Cash Advances and the Statement of Financial Position as of December 31, 2017;
*Strictly enforce the liquidation and collection of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;
*The Municipal Accountant shall demand for the liquidation of the above stated unliquidated cash advances;
*In the subsequent granting of cash advances and in order to prevent the accumulation of unliquidated cash advances, the Municipal Accountant shall send within ten (10) days before the expiration of the 30 days period written notices/reminders and letters enjoining the officers and employees to liquidate their travel cash advances.

